  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Sonographer - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_sonographer">Sonographer</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_sonographer">Sonographer</xref>
 is a specialised healthcare worker who performs diagnostic medical sonography, or diagnostic ultrasound.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_society_of_radiographers">Society of Radiographers</xref>
, administers a Public Voluntary Register for those individuals practising as 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_sonographer">Sonographers</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
For further information see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_society_of_radiographers">Society of Radiographers</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.sor.org/practice/ultrasound/register-sonographers"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Register of sonographers</xref>
.  </p>

